AB  - This paper analyzes the use of the balance of payments as a shock absorber in fixed and managed exchange rate regimes. The analysis is conducted in a monetary intergenerational model. It shows that the balance of payments can be used to smooth consumption and raise the welfare of individuals. The paper also justifies the stabilization of consumption as a policy goal, achieved through the balance of payments mechanism.
